      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;The one big thing about the panther nerf that still makes no sense to me is people complaining about the shaman doing to much dps... The shaman, the supposedly best buffing class (in soes description of a shaman) is buffing OTHER classes to do more dps.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Once&amp;nbsp;they fixed the pet procs then the shaman themselves could only add a max of&amp;nbsp;200 dps + there own melee and pets melee. (assuming they cast on themselves and their pets.) Probably less as they have to stop meleeing to cast the spell again, to slow, to debuff, etc... This certainly isn't any massive form of shaman dps - I can do more than that with 2 dots and some nukes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Now, yes it adds a lot of dps to groups and raids when cast on others but the shaman is not doing that dps - they are BUFFING (definitely in the shaman class role) others to do the damage. So apparently its ok for us to have a hp buff, an avoidance/dodge buff, etc... all kinds of buffs but its out of line for a shaman to have a damage buff? Avatar and might are supposedly damage buffs -panthers just the newest most powerful damage buff. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What folks are really mad about is that shaman finally got a buff that makes a noticeable difference and they are envious/angry about it. In time I was sure other buffing classes (like enchies) were going to have similar damage buffs added to their lines. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;They did balance the utility of this buff by making it very high mana cost for your typical shaman - maintainable of maybe 2 or 3 people max for an average shaman. The problem I guess is that 1 or 2% of the games shaman have exceptional gear/AA and can as a result hit far more people than your average shaman over a short period of time. This is, I admit, probably unbalanced for short fights (longer fights like say RC or xegony they will be oom and useless to quickly if they employ this strategy). While its nice to be able to burn your mana buffing the raid to do more dps I can see this as an issue for older fights not designed with this in mind.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;______________________________________________________________________&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
