&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I support making it group only - that prevents the top 1-2% from overly abusing this spell on raids. The increase in damage due to the raid being buffed to deliver it will scale by number of shaman spread about the raid in groups. (makes good sense)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I reluctantly can see the need for the pet fixes otherwise groups with shaman + pet classes will far outdamage other balanced groups... pets proccing almost 2 and a half times as much as PCs is wrong. I do like the idea of pets proccing a *slight* bit more than PCs to make it worth bringing out my dog but not 2 and a half times as much. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The change i do not&amp;nbsp;understand though is to reduce the proc... the first two changes will already scale back the buffing potential and damage delivered by the buff on pets. Why not give that a test run, parse some numbers and see how that works out? If its clearly overpowered still fine reduce it then. but three nerfs all at once seems a bit of an overcorrect for the first step of what you call 'retuning the spell.' Isn't the idea of retuning to adjust some, test, adjust some more if needed, test, repeat until right... In this case I guess retuning means nerf it into oblivion and see what happens... oh and extend the nerfed line down through the levels into a full spell line so all shaman can have extra spells in the back of their books they only situationally use. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;____________________________________________________________________&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
