      <description>Once again I repeat The spirit of the panther line of spells is getting nerfed because it is allowing a non-DPS class to do damage that is comparable to the true DPS classes.  If you feel it's just shamans getting singled out your wrong enchanters are also getting nerfed with this upcomming patch.  Charm is getting nerfed AGAIN and for the same purpose panther is getting nerfed.  It allows the enchanters to add DPS that is comparable to true-DPS classes.  In total there are 9 DPS classes and that is probabally more than there should be already by allowing the non-dps classes to make the already under desired and over abundant DPS classes even less desirable you are creating a serious in-game balance problem.  Certainally shamans will probabally become less desired than they are now but they will still be more desired than a magician or a berserker.  I think the real problem of the game is that there are classes that are over desireable in groups such as clerics and warriors.  There really should be some changes made so that all classes are more or less and equal desirability to other classes that fill the same role.  In short a druid should be as desirable as a cleric.  Paladins and shadow knights should be as desirable as warriors.  Berserkers should be as desirable as wizards or rogues.  All classes should be made similarly desirable as other classes but it should be done while keeping all classes unique.  So I do not want to see this being accomplished in the "EverQuest 2" way.  I would like to see it done in a more original way.  Yes I know that class balance and desirability is hard to work but I do believe that more can be done than is being done.  No class should feel worthless or undesirable.  No class should be over desirable and "the best".</description>
